'''_0_Types'''

'''
Python Arithmetic Operators:
==============================
| ------------ | -------------- | --------------------------------- | ------------------------ | ------------------ | ---------- | -------------------------------------------------------- |
| Operator     | Name           | Purpose (Simple Meaning)          | Mathematical Analogy     | Python Example     | Output     | Real-World Use Case                                      |
| ------------ | -------------- | --------------------------------- | ------------------------ | ------------------ | ---------- | -------------------------------------------------------- |
| `+`          | Addition       | Adds(Combines) values             | 6 + 4 = 10               | `10 + 5`           | `15`       | Total marks, total bill, bank deposits                   |
| `-`          | Subtraction    | Subtracts second value from first | 10 − 3 = 7               | `20 - 7`           | `13`       | Remaining balance, stock left, distance difference       |
| `*`          | Multiplication | Multiplies values                 | 3 × 4 = 12               | `6 * 4`            | `24`       | Price × quantity, area calculation, production count     |
| `/`          | Division       | Normal division (gives decimal)   | 15 ÷ 4 = 3.75            | `15 / 4`           | `3.75`     | Splitting amounts, averages, cost per item               |
| `%`          | Modulus        | Returns remainder                 | 25 mod 4 = 1             | `25 % 4`           | `1`        | Even/odd check, cycle resets, last digit extraction      |
| `//`         | Floor Division | Division removing decimal part    | floor(25 ÷ 4) = 6        | `25 // 4`          | `6`        | Counting full boxes, full batches, group formation       |
| `**`         | Exponent       | Raises to the power               | 2⁵ = 32                  | `2 ** 5`           | `32`       | Compound interest, growth rate, square/cube calculations |
| ------------ | -------------- | --------------------------------- | ------------------------ | ------------------ | ---------- | -------------------------------------------------------- |
'''